Health CS Mutahi Kagwe and Interior CS Fred Matian'gi on Wednesday held an inaugural meeting with the inter-faith council established to discuss ways to reopen places of worship while preventing the spread of Covid-19. Archbishop Anthony Muheria was last week appointed the chairman of the council. The first meeting was held at Ufungamano House in Nairobi. The state has been easing restrictions and on Tuesday, extended operation hours for eateries from 4pm to 7.30pm. Clerics have been calling for reopening of churches, saying all safety protocols will be adhered to.